# Lekka Stop Shop Design Language

Premium neighbourhood market — not a generic spaza UI. Experience quality = code quality.

## Identity

- Inspiration: real Westridge shop (bright red building, white wordmark). Do not redesign the building; translate its confidence into digital calm.
- Hero asset: `public/brand/lekka-stop-shop-hero.png`
- Full brief: `docs/LEKKA-STOP-SHOP-DESIGN.md`
- Tokens: `src/styles/lekka-tokens.css` under `.lekka` scope
- Do **not** restyle TammyShop Admin with Lekka red unless asked

## Customer feeling

Luxury neighbourhood market: trustworthy, calm, beautiful, expensive, easy. Customers should forget traditional convenience-store stigma.

## Colour (red = accent only)

- Brand red `#D0122B` — CTAs, key accents, never full-page floods
- Warm white bg `#FAF7F2`, pure white cards `#FFFFFF`
- Charcoal text `#1C1917`, warm grey `#78716C`
- Fresh produce green `#3F6F4A` sparingly
- Soft gold `#D4A017` only for light highlights (badge edge), not primary chrome

## Layout & UI

- Mobile-first, large touch targets, one-thumb checkout
- Full-bleed hero on storefront home; brand is hero-level (not nav-only)
- First viewport: brand + one headline + one support line + one CTA group + dominant image — no stats, schedules, promo chips, or floating badges on hero media
- Product cards: large image, short copy, clear ZAR price, elegant add-to-cart, generous space (cards OK as interaction containers)
- Nav: Apple-simple, sticky, large search, curated mega menus
- Rounded corners, subtle shadows, soft 150–280ms motion — no flashy animation
- Glass only on sticky nav/overlays when it improves clarity
- No clutter: no pill clusters, icon rows, or dashboard energy on marketing surfaces

## Photography

Natural light, fresh produce, warm wood/textures, Babylonstoren-adjacent grocery lifestyle. Prefer real shop/produce imagery over abstract gradients as the main visual idea.

## Typography

Expressive fonts (DM Sans + Fraunces or equivalent). Avoid Inter/Roboto/Arial/system defaults. Minimal text; photography leads.
